ttps://api.github.com/users/eholk/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eholk/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2021-06-25T16:08:38Z", "updated_at": "2021-07-08T06:46:41Z", "closed_at": "2021-07-08T06:46:41Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "<!-- Thanks for filing a \ud83d\udc1b bug report \ud83d\ude04! -->\r\n\r\n**Problem**\r\n<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->\r\n<!-- including what currently happens and what you expected to happen. -->\r\n\r\nThis came up during the discussion of https://github.com/rust-lang/cargo/issues/5034. Lints can be broken into rustc builtin lints, and lints supplied by a tool such as clippy. For clippy lints, they are prefixed by `clippy::`. The idea is that external lints are supposed to be ignored if the tool is not active. This works for lints controlled through attributes, such as `#![allow(clippy::foo)]`.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately the same thing doesn't work when allowing the lint through the command line, doing `rustc -A clippy::foo`.\r\n\r\n**Steps**\r\n<!-- The steps to reproduce the bug. -->\r\n1. Run `rustc -A clippy::foo test.rs`\r\n\r\n**Possible Solution(s)**\r\n<!-- Not obligatory, but suggest a fix/reason for the bug, -->\r\n<!-- or ideas how to implement the addition or change -->\r\n\r\nThe problem is at:\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/4733f32dbbbce7da5b06208a78af650be2db3001/compiler/rustc_lint/src/context.rs#L345\r\nThere is a hard-coded `None` passed in as the tool name in `check_lint_name`.\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_START$${\"user\":\"eholk\"}$$TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_END -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_END -->\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_END -->", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v